OL,5,Ccost
OL,7,FEnergy companies are required to work
OL,8,Fwith customers to agree on a payment
OL,9,Fplan they can afford, which could mean
OL,10,Fmore flexibility over how and at what
OL,11,Ftime people pay.
OL,13,FThey should take into account people's
OL,14,Fincome and outgoings, debts and
OL,15,Fpersonal circumstances, and an
OL,16,Festimate of how much energy will be
OL,17,Fused in future, for which regular
OL,18,Fmeter readings can help build a more
OL,19,Faccurate picture.
